2.5 Delegation of Duties via Subcontracting:

The Contractor shall have the right to engage third-party subcontractors for the performance of the Services, subject to the following conditions:

(a) The Contractor remains responsible for all obligations and liabilities arising from this Agreement, regardless of whether the Services are provided by the Contractor or its Subcontractors;

(b) The Contractor shall ensure that all Subcontractors are aware of their obligations under this Agreement and comply with these terms in full;

(c) The Contractor grants permission to any Subcontractor to act on its behalf for the purpose of performing the Services, but only to the extent necessary for the fulfillment of the Contractor's obligations under this Agreement. The Contractor shall remain liable for any acts or omissions of its Subcontractors;

(d) Any additional costs incurred by engaging Subcontractors shall be borne by the Contractor, and such costs may be recoverable from the Client as agreed upon in Section 4 (Costs and Payments);

(e) The Contractor shall provide the Client with the names and details of all Subcontractors at least 10 Business Days prior to their engagement.

The shift in this clause is that the Contractor maintains primary responsibility for obligations and liabilities under the Agreement, but can delegate tasks to subcontractors. The original clause may have implied shared or joint responsibility, while the revised clause clarifies that the Contractor remains solely responsible.
